onFault

public void onFault(IAeFault aFault,
                    java.util.Map aProcessProperties)
             throws AeBusinessProcessException
Callback when a fault arrives instead of the expected message.

Parameters:
aFault - The fault which has been received.
aProcessProperties - Business Process properties. This map will be null if the fault was generated from a correlation violation or an unmatched receive.
Throws:
AeBusinessProcessException - Allows the receiver to throw an exception.

getDurableReplyInfo

public IAeDurableReplyInfo getDurableReplyInfo()
Returns the durable reply information if the reply receiver is supports durable replies. Otherwise, returns null. Implementations that are durable must return an instance of IAeDurableReplyInfo.

Returns:
Durable reply information if available or null if not available.
